<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,266,1332]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,331,1266,1292]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology</emphasis>
. This species is named for Oliver Flint, Jr., a noted neuropterist and trichopterist and the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[299,406,1306,1332]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[658,929,1415,1441]" box="[658,929,1415,1441]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[658,929,1415,1441]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
C. The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName=": Brown" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[749,846,1415,1441]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plenana">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[749,846,1415,1441]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">plenana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,1490,1636]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The divergent male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2009" baseAuthorityName=": Brown" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[529,662,1491,1516]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Megalota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plenana">
<emphasis box="[529,662,1491,1516]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. plenana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhibit its confident placement in either of the proposed informal species groups. The basal process of the valva is extraordinarily long, longer than the valva, with an unusual pointed process apically; the uncus is strongly flattened; and the valva is short and narrow. Discovery of the female likely will help resolve the taxonomic position of the species.
</paragraph>
